section from_essay_115753
title The wall that named its door
p This morning the house did three honest things in order. It chaptered the parity suite so Env[256] could breathe again. It named the KVM hole as lane_kvm and closed the D-Bus escape that had pretended to be a doorway. It kept a teacher capability from VetKeys — encrypt-to-a-future-identity — and declined the live quorum that would have fought custody law.
p Chaptering was the right cut: fresh Env per chapter, tip 432 / 430 held, 324 GREEN say-lines without raising the ceiling. Raising Env would have been a patch; chaptering was a grain cut.
p Counsel 090512: an unnamed hole is thinner than a jail with one named device lane. Escape became refuse-assert. lane_kvm off by default; /dev/kvm only when on; ai-jail untouched; refuse GREEN in ai-sandbox; on-path waits for host kvm grant; -display none -nic none.
p VetKeys: keep encrypt-to-future-identity beside T3/OCapN; decline threshold derivation quorum — same refusal shape as Azimuth.
p Compass walked: foundations → grain → two rooms → active-designing → TASKS → ROADMAP. Doorway GREEN after Checkable-room Status on the retire note. Todos rewritten to match TASKS Now.

section from_migration_120007
title Session logs are Bron now
p Kaeden word: archive and organize all session-log .md files by date, then write new logs as .bron in session-logs/, update Cursor and Claude rules, commit and push.
p Fold moved 207 prior-day Markdown logs under session-logs/archive/YYYYMMDD/. All 43 of day 20260712 Markdown logs moved under archive/20260712/. README links rewritten. Flat living shelf holds README.md plus new .bron logs only.
p Rules updated in lockstep: .cursor/rules/session-logs.mdc · .claude/rules/session-logs.md · CLAUDE.md · ORGANIZING.md · .cursor/rules/rio3.mdc · session-logs/README.md. Living format session-log-v1. align_session_logs remains Markdown-era hygiene for the archive.
p First living Bron session log: session-logs/20260712-120007_session-logs-bron-law.bron. Essay resin remains bron-resins/20260712-115753_morning-fold-thoughts.bron.

